'''Spike''' is a 1983 [[platform game]] for the [[Vectrex]] video game system. The game uses [[voice synthesis]].<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|date=2011-04-15|title=Le Vectrex - Les jeux|url=http://www.jeuxvideo.com/dossiers/00014727/le-vectrex-les-jeux-003.htm|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419002803/http://www.jeuxvideo.com/dossiers/00014727/le-vectrex-les-jeux-003.htm|archive-date=2011-04-19|access-date=|website=Jeuxvideo.com|publisher=Webedia}}</ref><ref name="72-84">{{cite book|last=Weiss|first=Brett|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BzxTtml8Jq4C&q=spike+voice+synthesis&pg=PA279|title=Classic Home Video Games, 1972-1984: A Complete Reference Guide|date=2012-03-07|publisher=[[McFarland & Company]]|isbn=978-0786487554|location=|page=279}}</ref> ''Spike'' is included in the [[iOS]] Vectrex Regeneration app.<ref>{{cite web|last=Patterson|first=Blake|date=2012-11-28|title='Vectrex Regeneration' Review - iOS Gains a New...Old...Platform|url=http://toucharcade.com/2012/11/28/vectrex-regeneration-review-ios-gains-a-new-old-platform/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121201040540/http://toucharcade.com/2012/11/28/vectrex-regeneration-review-ios-gains-a-new-old-platform/|archive-date=2012-12-01|access-date=|website=[[TouchArcade]]|publisher=TouchArcade.com, LLC.}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The player must navigate a tiny creature named Spike through chasms and ladders while avoiding enemies and endless pits. The player must collect Molly's bows to unlock doors and reach the final level to save Molly from the boss named Spud and bring her home.

